data.title: Memphis Grizzlies Roster
data.meta_description: Memphis Grizzlies scores, news, schedule, players, stats, rumors, depth charts and more on RealGM.com
data.text:
Jevon Carter was selected as the #2 pick in the Second Round of the 2018 NBA Draft by the Memphis Grizzlies. Jevon Carter signed a multi-year contract with the Memphis Grizzlies on July 15, 2018.

Mike Conley was selected as the #4 pick in the First Round of the 2007 NBA Draft by the Memphis Grizzlies. Mike Conley signed a multi-year contract with the Memphis Grizzlies on July 29, 2007. Mike Conley signed a multi-year extension with the Memphis Grizzlies on November 2, 2010. Mike Conley re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Memphis Grizzlies on July 14, 2016.

Jaren Jackson, Jr. was selected as the #4 pick in the First Round of the 2018 NBA Draft by the Memphis Grizzlies. Jaren Jackson, Jr. signed a multi-year contract with the Memphis Grizzlies on July 1, 2018.

Draft Rights to Dillon Brooks, the #15 pick in the Second Round of the 2017 NBA Draft, were acquired by the Memphis Grizzlies from the Houston Rockets on June 22, 2017. Dillon Brooks signed a multi-year contract with the Memphis Grizzlies on July 21, 2017.

Draft Rights to Ivan Rabb, the #5 pick in the Second Round of the 2017 NBA Draft, were acquired by the Memphis Grizzlies from the Orlando Magic on June 22, 2017. Ivan Rabb signed a multi-year contract with the Memphis Grizzlies on September 20, 2017.

Avery Bradley was acquired in a trade by the Memphis Grizzlies from the Los Angeles Clippers on February 7, 2019.

Tyler Dorsey was acquired in a trade by the Memphis Grizzlies from the Atlanta Hawks on February 7, 2019.

Justin Holiday was acquired in a trade by the Memphis Grizzlies from the Chicago Bulls on January 3, 2019.

C.J. Miles was acquired in a trade by the Memphis Grizzlies from the Toronto Raptors on February 7, 2019.

Jonas Valanciunas was acquired in a trade by the Memphis Grizzlies from the Toronto Raptors on February 7, 2019.

Delon Wright was acquired in a trade by the Memphis Grizzlies from the Toronto Raptors on February 7, 2019.

Kyle Anderson signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Memphis Grizzlies on July 8, 2018.

Bruno Caboclo signed a contract with the Memphis Grizzlies on January 24, 2019. Bruno Caboclo re-signed to a contract as a free agent with the Memphis Grizzlies on February 3, 2019. Bruno Caboclo re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Memphis Grizzlies on February 13, 2019.

Joakim Noah signed a contract as a free agent with the Memphis Grizzlies on December 4, 2018.

Chandler Parsons signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Memphis Grizzlies on July 7, 2016.

Tyler Zeller signed a contract as a free agent with the Memphis Grizzlies on April 5, 2019.
